- The class AuthResources is annotated with @Path("/api/v0/ops/auth"), and the method createRole is annotated with @Path("/role/") and @POST, yielding the full REST endpoint path /api/v0/ops/auth/role/.
- The handler is the createRole method in the AuthResources class, i.e., com.datastax.mgmtapi.resources.AuthResources#createRole.
- The method’s implementation is within the same source file (the logic is defined directly in this file, even though it delegates request handling to the imported handle(...) helper).
- The path string "/role/" is a literal defined in the source code, and combined with the class-level path gives a concrete full path.
- The path is not a prefix for other paths (no additional subpaths defined under it in this file).
- The path is not derived from a framework naming convention; it’s explicitly provided.
- This entry represents a RESTful API endpoint (JAX-RS annotations used).
- It is not a testing endpoint.
